messages.content: ComfyUI-nevysha-top-menu is a simple sidebar tweak for ComfyUI that forces the menu to the top of the screen.
How is the installation process for ComfyUI-nevysha-top-menu described?
The installation process for ComfyUI-nevysha-top-menu is described as really quick and dirty, and it may break with some ComfyUI setups.
What is the first step in installing ComfyUI-nevysha-top-menu?
The first step in installing ComfyUI-nevysha-top-menu is to go to your ComfyUI 'custom_nodes' directory.
What is the second step in installing ComfyUI-nevysha-top-menu?
The second step in installing ComfyUI-nevysha-top-menu is to clone the repository: https://github.com/Nevysha/ComfyUI-nevysha-top-menu.
What is the third step in installing ComfyUI-nevysha-top-menu?
The third step in installing ComfyUI-nevysha-top-menu is to run the command 'n_n'.
What is the license for ComfyUI-nevysha-top-menu?
The license for ComfyUI-nevysha-top-menu is GPL-3.0.
Is there a Ko-fi link associated with ComfyUI-nevysha-top-menu?
Yes, there is a Ko-fi link (https://ko-fi.com/G2G2L55CD) associated with ComfyUI-nevysha-top-menu.
